children.subject:
Thanks for the comprehensive info!

In terms of my chances of getting into the class as a data science major, would you happen to have any insight into this?
I don't know honestly but from what I understand most people get into the class.

Workload is not too bad, 4 homeworks and a final project. However, the homeworks can be time consuming, each one took me 3-4 days of focused work. Final Project can be time consuming since you have to try something novel and interesting—be sure to start early and give your models enough time to train. 

You definitely need to have strong mathematical maturity to do well in this course. The neural networks and RL portions of CS 188 should be helpful, and you should also have strong foundations in linear algebra, probability, and vector calculus. Courses like math 53, math 110, ee 127, and stat 140/ee 126 are a good background. 

Also, for what it's worth, you can watch all the recorded lectures from last spring here: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL_iWQOsE6TfVmKkQHucjPAoRtIJYt8a5A
